%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Don't%20want%20Russia%20to%20successfully%20invade%20your%20country%3F%20Then%20do%20this.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ukrainian%20troops%20defeated%20Russia's%20attempt%20to%20seize%20Hostomel%20airport%20near%20Kyiv%20in%20the%20war's%20opening%20days%20in%202022.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65de44b6ce7f1785b2e44be4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221304%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20troops%20defeated%20Russia's%20attempt%20to%20seize%20Hostomel%20airport%20near%20Kyiv%20in%20the%20war's%20opening%20days%20in%202022.%3Cp%3EDogukan%20Keskinkilic%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERussia's%20attempt%20to%20seize%20Hostomel%20airport%20in%202022%20was%20part%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bwell-established%20playbook.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BAppreciation%20of%20this%20playbook%20is%20key%20for%20states%20who%20might%20find%20themselves%20in%20the%20crosshairs%2C%26quot%3B%20experts%20wrote.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEven%20though%20Russia%20may%20dwarf%20a%20small%20state%2C%20that%20doesn't%20guarantee%20a%20successful%20airport%20seizure.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHere's%20some%20advice%20for%20nations%20who%20don't%20want%20Russian%20troops%20as%20uninvited%20guests%3A%20Guard%20your%20airport.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat's%20the%20recommendation%20from%20two%20American%20defense%20experts%20who%20point%20to%20a%20pattern%20in%20Russian%20operations%20over%20the%20last%2050%20years%3A%20when%20the%20Kremlin%20wants%20to%20occupy%20another%20nation%2C%20it%20goes%20for%20the%20airport.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERussia's%20failed%20attempt%20to%20seize%20Kyiv's%20Hostomel%20airport%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%202022%20Ukraine%20invasion%20was%20part%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bwell-established%20playbook%2C%26quot%3B%20Kevin%20Stringer%20and%20Heather%20Gregg%20wrote%20in%20an%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmwi.westpoint.edu%2Fdisrupting-moscows-invasion-playbook-lessons-from-prague-to-kyiv%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eessay%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20West%20Point's%20Modern%20War%20Institute.%20Moscow%20sent%20commandos%20and%20paratroopers%20to%20seize%20airports%20in%20Prague%20in%201968%2C%20Kabul%20in%201979%20and%20Sevastopol%20in%202014%2C%20to%20facilitate%20an%20advance%20by%20ground%20troops%20invading%20across%20the%20border.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BAn%20appreciation%20of%20this%20playbook%20is%20key%20for%20states%20who%20might%20find%20themselves%20in%20the%20crosshairs%20of%20future%20Russian%20aggression%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20essay%20warned.%20The%20strategy%20can%20work%20with%20blistering%20speed%20as%20elite%20assault%20troops%20seize%20the%20airport%20to%20create%20an%20aerial%20beachhead.%20Air%20transports%20can%20then%20fly%20in%20reinforcements%20to%20expand%20the%20airhead%2C%20while%20waiting%20to%20link%20up%20with%20armored%20columns%20pouring%20across%20the%20border.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERussian%20operations%20follow%20a%20typical%20sequence%2C%20according%20to%20the%20essay.%20%26quot%3BPositioning%20conventional%20forces%20on%20the%20borders%20of%20the%20targeted%20country%20to%20amplify%20political%20pressure%20and%20organize%20for%20invasion%3B%20infiltrating%20special%20operations%20(Spetsnaz)%20units%20to%20prepare%20and%20spearhead%20the%20incursion%3B%20seizing%20a%20strategic%20airport%20through%20airborne%20units%3B%20and%20airlanding%20additional%20assault%20troops%20to%20secure%20the%20battlespace%20and%20decapitate%20the%20national%20government%20in%20conjunction%20with%20the%20already%20inserted%20special%20operations%20units.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20airport%20invasion%20force%20typically%20comprises%20a%20%26quot%3Bspecial%20forces%20detachment%20to%20achieve%20surprise%2C%20followed%20with%20a%20battalion-sized%20element%20to%20pave%20the%20way%20for%20at%20least%20a%20brigade%20to%20follow%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Stringer%2C%20a%20retired%20US%20Army%20colonel%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20A%20Russian%20brigade%20typically%20numbers%20about%204%2C000%20paratroops.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20strategy%20doesn't%20always%20work.%20The%202022%20Kyiv%20air%20assault%20was%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwarontherocks.com%2F2023%2F08%2Fthe-battle-of-hostomel-airport-a-key-moment-in-russias-defeat-in-kyiv%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efiasco%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%20air%20strikes%20failed%20to%20suppress%20Ukrainian%20air%20defenses%20that%20shot%20down%20numerous%20helicopters%2C%20close%20air%20support%20for%20the%20airhead%20was%20lacking%2C%20and%20Ukrainian%20forces%20quickly%20counterattacked%20the%20300%20beleaguered%20paratroopers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20other%20Russian%20airport%20takedowns%20have%20been%20largely%20successful.%20The%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdefenceindepth.co%2F2018%2F08%2F20%2Fthe-end-of-the-prague-spring-fifty-years-on%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EPrague%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20attack%20helped%20Warsaw%20Pact%20forces%20to%20occupy%20Czechoslovakia%20with%20minimal%20fighting%20and%20casualties.%20The%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rferl.org%2Fa%2Fpoisonings-assassination-and-a-coup-the-secret-soviet-invasion-of-afghanistan%2F30347141.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EKabul%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20attack%2C%20which%20aimed%20to%20topple%20Afghan%20president%20Hafizullah%20Amin%2C%20was%20bloodier%3A%20Hundreds%20of%20Afghans%2C%20as%20well%20as%20KGB%20and%20Spetznaz%20commandos%2C%20died%20during%20an%20assault%20on%20the%20presidential%20palace%20that%20ended%20with%20Russian%20troops%20killing%20Amin.%20At%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.economist.com%2Feastern-approaches%2F2014%2F03%2F01%2Fedging-closer-to-war%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESevastopol%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Spetznaz%20units%20(the%20notorious%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Fwatch-out-for-little-green-men%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3Blittle%20green%20men%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20unmarked%20uniforms)%20seized%20two%20airfields%20in%20a%20mostly%20bloodless%20operation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russian%20soldiers%20take%20their%20position%20upon%20their%20landing%20at%20an%20unspecified%20location%20in%20Ukraine%20in%20this%20image%20released%20on%20Dec.%206%2C%202022.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65de472290413ab8e1d73c47%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221115%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERussian%20soldiers%20take%20their%20position%20upon%20their%20landing%20at%20an%20unspecified%20location%20in%20Ukraine%20in%20this%20image%20released%20on%20Dec.%206%2C%202022.%3Cp%3ERussian%20Defense%20Ministry%20Press%20Service%2FAP%20Photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGiven%20that%20seizing%20airports%20has%20worked%20for%20Russia%20in%20the%20past%2C%20it's%20reasonable%20to%20assume%20the%20Kremlin%20will%20use%20similar%20methods%20against%20other%20potential%20targets%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Baltic%20States%2C%20Moldova%20or%20Georgia.%20But%20that's%20easier%20said%20than%20done%20for%20small%20nations%20with%20small%20militaries.%20%26quot%3BRussia%20may%20have%20its%20hands%20full%20in%20Ukraine%20right%20now%2C%20but%20adequately%20preparing%20for%20Russia's%20invasion%20playbook%20takes%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20essay%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%2C%20combined%20with%20Russia's%20pattern%20of%20invading%20a%20country%20and%20deposing%20its%20leadership%2C%20makes%20it%20critical%20for%20vulnerable%20countries%20to%20take%20measures%20to%20counter%20the%20threat.%20For%20countries%20like%20Moldova%20and%20Georgia%2C%20this%20preparation%20is%20no%20small%20feat%2C%20given%20that%20both%20have%20Russian%20troops%20already%20in%20their%20country%2C%20are%20relatively%20small%2C%20and%20are%20faced%20with%20a%20range%20of%20resource%20constraints.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20authors%20suggest%20several%20solutions%20that%20aren't%20ruinously%20expensive.%20The%20first%20is%20to%20deploy%20special%20military%20units%20to%20defend%20key%20airports.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Ukrainians%20left%20elements%20of%20the%204th%20Rapid%20Reaction%20Brigade%20of%20the%20National%20Guard%20at%20the%20Antonov%20Airport%2C%20despite%20the%20overwhelming%20need%20for%20Ukrainian%20troops%20to%20confront%20the%20Russian%20invasion%20at%20its%20borders%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20essay%20noted.%20%26quot%3BThis%20unit%20of%20around%20three%20hundred%20troops%20succeeded%20in%20frustrating%20the%20Russian%20forces'%20seizure%20of%20the%20airport%20and%20rendered%20the%20airstrip%20unusable%2C%20foiling%20subsequent%20Russian%20efforts%20to%20land%20forces%20and%20seize%20the%20capital.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStringer%20points%20to%20a%20special%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3Eairport%20defense%20regiment%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20Switzerland%20stationed%20at%20Zurich%20Airport%20during%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20as%20a%20good%20model.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20brigade-sized%20element%20of%20approximately%203%2C000%20personnel%2C%20primarily%20local%20reservists%20on%20standby.%20It%20consisted%20of%20four%20operational%20battalions%20armed%20with%20machine%20guns%2C%2081-mm%20and%2060-mm%20mortars%2C%20armored%20personnel%20carriers%20with%2020-mm%20cannon%2C%20and%20Stinger%20anti-aircraft%20missiles.%20Airport%20vehicles%20could%20be%20used%20to%20block%20the%20runway.%20I%20think%20this%20model%20would%20be%20both%20pragmatic%C2%A0and%20affordable%20for%20a%20small%20state%20today.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20though%20Russia%20may%20dwarf%20a%20small%20state%20in%20military%20power%2C%20that%20doesn't%20guarantee%20a%20successful%20airport%20seizure.%20Lightly%20armed%20airborne%20troops%20have%20historically%20been%20vulnerable%20to%20anti-aircraft%20defenses%20as%20they%20fly%20in%20and%20counterattacks%20by%20the%20defender%20before%20they%20can%20organize%20a%20ground%20position.%20%26quot%3BIf%20the%20defense%20is%20prepared%2C%20the%20Russians%20are%20vulnerable%2C%26quot%3B%20Stringer%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20vulnerability%20increases%20if%20they%20do%20not%20have%20air%20superiority%20over%20the%20airfield.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20Russian%20troops%20do%20manage%20to%20capture%20an%20airport%2C%20the%20defender's%20best%20option%20is%20%26quot%3Bimmediate%20counterattack%20to%20dislodge%20the%20assaulting%20force%20and%20block%20the%20runway%20in%20order%20to%20prevent%20reinforcement%20and%20expansion%20of%20the%20airhead%2C%26quot%3B%20Stringer%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20US%20and%20Europe%20can%20also%20assist%20vulnerable%20nations%20in%20defending%20their%20airports.%20%26quot%3BThe%20United%20States%20military%20has%20several%20units%20dedicated%20to%20seizing%20or%20securing%20airstrips%2C%20particularly%20within%20the%20Army's%2075th%20Ranger%20Regiment%20and%20Air%20Force%20special%20operations%20forces%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20essay%20said.%20%26quot%3BThese%20units%20could%20provide%20valuable%20training%20on%20how%20to%20plan%20for%20and%20disrupt%20a%20Russian%20assault%20on%20critical%20airports.%20Similar%20capabilities%20exist%20within%20European%20special%20operations%20and%20conventional%20forces%2C%20including%20countries%20with%20total%20defense%20plans%2C%20such%20as%20Finland%20and