talians%20worry%20about%20the%20outsize%20role%20Americans%20play%2C%20especially%20in%20Florence.%20Dozens%20of%20American%20universities%20have%20outposts%20in%20the%20city%2C%20attracting%20roughly%2015%2C000%20college%20students%20each%20year.%20American%20tourists%20love%20Florence%2C%20but%20their%20presence%20has%20consequences%20%E2%80%94%20like%20a%20sharp%20increase%20in%20the%20number%20of%20Airbnbs%20that%20the%20Associated%20Press%20reported%20makes%20it%20hard%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Feuropean-tourism-summer-travel-pandemic-recovery-ee4416b151618fce3bf6cb5e3ff24d99%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elocal%20doctors%20to%20afford%20to%20live%3C%2Fa%3E%20near%20the%20city%20center.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20downsides%20to%20the%20region's%20popularity%2C%20some%20residents%20added%2C%20include%20being%20priced%20out%20by%20the%20deeper-pocketed%20newcomers%2C%20and%20more%20mundane%20concerns%20like%20traffic%20and%20crowds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20Americans%2C%20though%2C%20Tuscany%20remains%20a%20dream.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavis%20said%20locals%20often%20assume%20she's%20on%20vacation.%20When%20she%20tells%20them%20that%20she%20owns%20a%20home%20in%20Boccheggiano%2C%20they're%20confused.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20like%2C%20'Why%20would%20an%20American%20want%20to%20come%20and%20live%20in%20such%20a%20tiny%20town%3F'%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20tell%20them%20it's%20the%20quality%20of%20life%20or%20it's%20the%20slow%20pace%20or%20the%20people%20%E2%80%94%20or%20whatever%20%E2%80%94%20they%20just%20say%2C%20'Oh%2C%20we've%20always%20dreamed%20of%20moving%20to%20California.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAmerican%20interest%20in%20Tuscany%20is%20on%20the%20rise%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThroughout%20the%20pandemic%20years%2C%20Americans%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-moved-to-istanbul-loves-it-cheap-cost-of-living-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eflocked%20to%20Europe%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20seeking%20more%20affordable%20lifestyles%20with%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-from-us-europe-escape-american-hustle-culture-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emanageable%20paces%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETuscany%20has%20its%20own%20charm.%20Relatively%20sequestered%20from%20the%20hustle%20and%20bustle%20of%20Rome%20or%20the%20crowded%20canals%20and%20alleyways%20of%20Venice%2C%20Tuscany's%20rise%20in%2021st-century%20popular%20culture%20is%20often%20tied%20to%20Frances%20Mayer's%201996%20memoir%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdiane-lane-says-no-under-the-tuscan-sun-sequel-2020-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUnder%20the%20Tuscan%20Sun%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20At%20Home%20in%20Italy%2C%26quot%3B%20about%20a%20woman%20who%20moves%20to%20Italy%20after%20a%20divorce%2C%20buys%20a%20dilapidated%20farmhouse%2C%20and%20finds%20love%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%2030%20years%20later%2C%20it's%20easy%20to%20see%20the%20region's%20continuing%20allure.%20Numbeo%2C%20a%20data%20provider%20that%20uses%20self-reported%20stats%20to%20track%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20worldwide%2C%20says%20it's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.numbeo.com%2Fcost-of-living%2Fcountry_result.jsp%3Fcountry%3DItaly%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enearly%2020%25%20cheaper%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20live%20in%20Italy%20than%20in%20the%20US%2C%20on%20average.%20Inflation%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cia.gov%2Fthe-world-factbook%2Fcountries%2Fitaly%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20also%20risen%20at%20a%20slower%20clip%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20average%20life%20expectancy%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cia.gov%2Fthe-world-factbook%2Fcountries%2Funited-states%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20few%20years%20longer%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMichele%20Capecchi%2C%20a%20lawyer%20in%20Florence%20who%20helps%20Americans%20secure%20Italian%20citizenship%2C%20opens%20his%20inbox%20every%20Monday%20morning%20to%20find%20about%20150%20new%20emails%20%E2%80%94%20roughly%20a%20third%20of%20which%20are%20from%20Americans%20seeking%20help%20in%20relocating%20to%20Italy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20read%20about%20Italy%2C%20and%20the%20sun%2C%20the%20culture.%20Of%20course%2C%20the%20bureaucracy%20doesn't%20help%2C%26quot%3B%20Capecchi%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-living-in-italy-thankful-for-healthcare-for-daughter-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estandard%20of%20living%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20%E2%80%94%20there%20are%20multiple%20factors%20that%20make%20Italy%20very%20attractive%20for%20a%20lot%20of%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmericans%20can%20stay%20in%20Italy%20visa-free%20for%20up%20to%2090%20days.%20After%20that%2C%20non-residents%20need%20to%20obtain%20a%20permit%20of%20stay%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftravel.state.gov%2Fcontent%2Ftravel%2Fen%2Finternational-travel%2FInternational-Travel-Country-Information-Pages%2FItaly.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAll%2520non%252Dresidents%2520are%2520required%2Cstay%2520(permesso%2520di%2520soggiorno).%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20Department%20of%20State%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EErin%20Lewis%2C%20an%20American%20yoga%20instructor%20who%20has%20lived%20in%20Italy%20full-time%20since%202015%2C%20currently%20lives%20near%20the%20Tuscan%20city%20of%20Chiusi.%20Lewis%2C%2043%2C%20and%20her%20partner%2C%20whom%20she%20met%20in%20Italy%2C%20bought%20land%20and%20broke%20ground%20on%20a%20house%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20had%20no%20Italian%20blood%2C%20but%20I%20just%20felt%20like%20somewhere%20deep%20down%2C%20maybe%20I%20was%20an%20Etruscan%20in%20a%20past%20life%20or%20something%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lewis%2C%20referring%20to%20an%20ancient%20people%20who%20inhabited%20the%20area%20millennia%20ago.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20felt%20totally%20at%20home%20and%20wanted%20to%20find%20a%20way%20back.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20posing%20by%20a%20home.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e2086090413ab8e1d84bcc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221886%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELewis%20has%20lived%20in%20Italy%20full-time%20since%202015.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Erin%20Lewis%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20more%20American%20friends%20of%20Lewis'%20have%20sought%20her%20advice%20about%20making%20the%20move%20to%20Italy%20themselves.%20Many%20are%20hoping%20to%20get%20away%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-i-moved-from-texas-to-italy-right-before-retirement-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerica's%20tenuous%20political%20landscape%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20plague%20of%20gun%20violence%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20number%20of%20Americans%20registering%20to%20live%20in%20Italy%20is%20indeed%20rising%2C%20data%20show.%20It%20jumped%20from%203%2C951%20in%202019%20up%20to%206%2C813%20in%202022%20(the%20most%20recent%20year%20for%20which%20data%20is%20available)%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0a%2042%25%20increase%20in%20just%20four%20years%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Italian%20National%20Institute%20of%20Statistics.%20The%20number%20of%20Americans%20specifically%20calling%20the%20region%20of%20Tuscany%20home%20increased%20by%206%25%20between%202019%20and%202023%2C%20growing%20from%202%2C193%20four%20years%20ago%20to%202%2C323%20now%2C%20according%20to%20the%20institute's%20foreign%20census%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EItalian%20home-listing%20website%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fgate-away.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGate-away.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20told%20BI%20that%2029%25%20of%20its%20inquiries%20in%202023%20came%20from%20Americans.%20And%2020%25%20of%20those%20inquiries%20%E2%80%94%20the%20most%20of%20any%20region%20%E2%80%94%20were%20for%20properties%20in%20Tuscany.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDanilo%20Romolini%2C%20a%20specialist%20in%20Italian%20luxury%20home%20sales%20at%20Christie's%20International%20Real%20Estate%2C%20said%20that%2040%25%20of%20new%20requests%20he%20fields%20come%20from%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0a%20figure%20that's%20been%20on%20the%20rise%20during%20the%20pandemic%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmboldened%20by%20the%20dollar's%20recent%20strength%2C%20he%20added%2C%20some%20buyers%20are%20even%20confident%20enough%20to%20pull%20the%20trigger%2C%20sight-unseen.%20Recently%2C%20he%20sold%20a%20more%20than%204%2C000-square%20foot%20farmhouse%20with%20sweeping%20views%20of%20the%20Val%20di%20Chiana%20and%20a%20listing%20price%20of%201.6%20million%20euros%20(%241.7%20million)%20to%20an%20automobile-industry%20professional%20from%20Austin%2C%20Texas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ELocals'%20response%20to%20the%20influx%20of%20Americans%20is%20mixed%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELuca%20Tudor%20runs%20AJ%20Tuscany%2C%20an%20upscale%20jewelry%20boutique%20on%20Montepulciano's%20steep%20main%20artery%2C%20Via%20di%20Gracciano%20nel%20Corso.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETudor%2C%20who's%20called%20the%20region%20home%20since%20he%20was%2012%2C%20says%20the%20arrival%20of%20so%20many%20Americans%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%20a%20phenomenon%20that's%20become%20%26quot%3Bbigger%20and%20bigger%20in%20the%20last%20two%2C%20three%20years%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0is%20helping%20keep%20the%20ancient%20cities%20that%20dot%20the%20landscape%20from%20turning%20into%20ghost%20towns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20people%20love%20what%20is%20called%20'piazza%20life%2C'%26quot%3B%20Tudor%2C%2033%2C%20explained%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhich%20means%20getting%20into%20your%20own%20apartment%20and%20never%20taking%20the%20car%20again.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESam%20D'Avanzo%2C%20a%2029-year-old%20Florence%20native%20who%20owns%20a%20nightclub%20and%20concierge%20travel%20service%20in%20the%20city%2C%20said%20the%20influx%20of%20American%20residents%20has%20buoyed%20local%20lifestyle%20and%20entertainment%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmericans%20may%20eat%20out%20as%20often%20as%20two%20or%20three%20times%20a%20week%2C%20he%20said%2C%20whereas%20Tuscans%20might%20only%20dine%20out%20a%20few%20times%20a%20month.%20In%20a%20typical%20meal%2C%20he%20added%2C%20Americans%20tend%20to%20spend%2030%25%20to%2040%25%20more%20on%20food%20and%20drink%20than%20Italian%20diners%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20look%20through%20an%20arch%20at%20a%20town%20square%20in%20Tuscany%2C%20Italy.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e25ba9ce7f1785b2e5ad72%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPiazza%20dell'Anfiteatro%20in%20Lucca%2C%20Italy.%3Cp%3EFrank%20Bienewald%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20family%20friends%20of%20D'Avanzo's%20from%20Houston%2C%20Texas%2C%20recently%20bought%20a%20five-bedroom%20apartment%20in%20Florence's%20historic%20center%2C%20he%20said.%20Now%20they%20live%20there%20year-round.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20all%20locals%20seem%20so%20enthused.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20everyone%20who%20will%20say%20that%20international%20investors%20or%20people%20deciding%20to%20move%20their%20life%20here%20is%20a%20good%20thing%20for%20our%20economy%2C%20you%20will%20find%20someone%20there%20that%20says%20they%20are%20actually%20depriving%20Tuscany%20or%20local%20citizens%20of%20entire%20pieces%20of%20their%20city%2C%26quot%3B%20Capecchi%2C%20the%20Italian%20lawyer%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20area%20where%20tensions%20appear%20to%20be%20running%20high%20is%20in%20schools%2C%20which%20have%20become%20so%20inundated%20with%20inquiries%20from%20foreign%20families%20that%20some%20have%20been%20relegated%20to%20waiting%20lists%2C%20Capecchi%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20years%20past%2C%20many%20American%20families%20would%20come%20for%20a%20year%20or%20two%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmistakes-americans-make-when-moving-to-italy-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esoak%20up%20Italian%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20moving%20home%2C%20but%20now%20some%20are%20staying%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20International%20School%20of%20Florence%2C%20which%20has%20served%20Florence's%20English-speaking%20community%20since%201952%2C%2027%25%20of%20this%20year's%20class%20is%20made%20up%20of%20American%20students%2C%20versus%2023%25%20last%20year%20and%20fewer%20than%2020%25%20during%20pre-COVID%20times%2C%20according%20to%20the%20school's%20admissions%20office.%20In%20conversations%20with%20administrators%2C%20the%20admissions%20office%20added%2C%20parents%20often%20cite%20quality%20of%20life%20and%20alarm%20over%20US%20school%20safety%20as%20reasons%20they've%20made%20the%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20reached%20by%20a%20lot%20of%20families%20who%20say%2C%20'We're%20sick%20and%20tired%20of%20having%20our%20kids%20having%20to%20do%20shooting%20drills%20in%20the%20school%2C'%26quot%3B%20Capecchi%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20some%20families%20have%20likened%20attending%20US%20elementary%20schools%20with%20metal%20detectors%20to%20going%20to%20the%20airport.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20private%20Facebook%20groups%20for%20Italians%2C%20some%20locals%20vent%20about%20more%20cumbersome%20summertime%20traffic%20getting%20in%20pedestrians'%20way.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20locals%20say%20that%20a%20place%20like%20Montepulciano%20cannot%20handle%20all%20those%20tourists%20because%20it's%20a%20small%20city%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Tudor%2C%20the%20jeweler.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETourism%20alone%2C%20though%2C%20doesn't%20seem%20to%20account%20for%20the%20increase%20in%20Americans%20since%20pandemic%20lockdowns%20started%20to%20subside.%20In%20fact%2C%20tourism%20numbers%20haven't%20quite%20rebounded%20to%20pre-COVID%20levels%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20Federalberghi%2C%20an%20Italian%20hospitality%20industry%20trade%20association.%20In%202019%2C%20before%20the%20pandemic%2C%20Tuscany%20received%201.05%20million%20tourists.%20In%202022%2C%20it%20welcomed%20956%2C000%20visitors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Pedestrians%20and%20bicyclists%20navigating%20through%20a%20town%20square%20in%20Florence%2C%20Italy.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e2075f6080194819fba441%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20pedestrian-friendly%20town%20square%20in%20Florence%2C%20Italy.%3Cp%3EMaremagnum%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20American%20residents%20who%20are%20staying%20for%20the%20long%20term%20seem%20aware%20of%20the%20effect%20they've%20having.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20locals%20have%20seen%20themselves%20priced%20out%20of%20rentals%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jupe%2C%20who%20returned%20to%20Florence%20in%202023%20after%20a%20three-year%20stint%20in%20Switzerland.%20She%20conceded%20that%20some%20locals%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-bought-a-cheap-house-in-italy-sicily-listings-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estruggle%20to%20find%20affordable%20properties%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20rent%20or%20buy%3A%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20so%20many%20people%20that%20want%20to%20live%20here.%20And%20so%2C%20of%20course%2C%20that%20can%20cause%20a%20bit%20of%20resentment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ENewcomers%20also%20bring%20new%20opportunities%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBendetta%20Ercolani%2C%2031%2C%20lives%20in%20an%20apartment%20block%20in%20Montepulciano%20where%20she's%20the%20only%20Italian.%20One%20other%20resident%20is%20Albanian%2C%20she%20said%2C%20while%20the%20remaining%20two%20units%20are%20home%20to%20American%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20family%20owns%20a%20winery%20that%20has%20used%20traditional%20methods%20to%20produce%20their%20vintages%20for%20generations.%20But%20newcomers%20from%20the%20States%20have%20even%20local%20stalwarts%20like%20the%20Ercolanis%20contemplating%20new%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20Cantina%20Ercolani%20debuted%20its%20first%20sparkling%20wine.%20It%20was%20a%20decision%20partly%20influenced%20by%20Americans%2C%20Ercolani%20said%2C%20who%20were%20seeking%20a%20thirst%20quencher%20to%20cool%20off%20during%20sweltering%20Tuscan%20summers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sparkler%20is%20made%20entirely%20from%20Sangiovese%20grapes%20harvested%20on%20the%20family's%20land.%20At%20first%2C%20she%20said%2C%20Cantina%20Ercolani%20tested%20a%20production%20of%20about%203%2C000%20bottles%2C%20and%20now%20it's%20scaling%20up%2C%20with%20another%205%2C000%20on%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmericans%2C%20Ercolani%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bspend%20money%20and%20they%20appreciate%20the%20quality%20of%20the%20food%20and%20the%20wine%20that%20we%20have.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTuscany%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added%2C%20is%20%26quot%3Blike%20a%20brand.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftuscany-americans-moving-italy-cost-of-living-slow-pace-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709374621000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65d78685f533b039a88606f3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftuscany-americans-moving-italy-cost-of-living-slow-pace-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22People%20are%20moving%20to%20the%20region%20known%20for%20wine%2C%20food%2C%20and%20art%20for%20reasons%20from%20a%20lower%20cost%20of%20living%20to%20a%20desire%20to%20live%20more%20slowly.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jpandy%40insider.com%20(Jordan%20Pandy%2CReed%20Alexander)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftuscany-americans-moving-italy-cost-of-living-slow-pace-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20nutritionist%20who%20cut%20down%20on%20ultra-processed%20foods%20shares%20what%20he%20used%20to%20eat%20for%20breakfast%20and%20what%20he%20has%20now%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Nutritionist%20Rob%20Honson%20(left)%20Man%20kneading%20dough.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e1f2306080194819fb902e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERob%20Hobson%20cuts%20out%20ultra-processed%20foods%20from%20his%20diet%20wherever%20possible.%3Cp%3ERob%20Hobson%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EUltra-processed%20foods%20have%20been%20linked%20to%20a%20range%20of%20health%20problems.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENutritionist%20Rob%20Hobson%20eats%20as%20few%20UPFs%20as%20possible%20by%20cooking%20from%20scratch.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20is%20what%20his%20breakfast%20looked%20like%20before%20and%20after%20making%20the%20change.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20nutritionist%20who%20eats%20as%20little%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freduce-ultra-processed-foods-nutritionist-tips-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eultra-processed%20food%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20possible%20and%20wrote%20a%20book%20on%20how%20others%20can%20do%20the%20same%20shared%20what%20he%20ate%20for%20breakfast%20before%20changing%20his%20diet%2C%20and%20what%20he%20eats%20now.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERob%20Hobson%2C%20a%20UK-based%20nutritionist%20with%2018%20years%20of%20experience%2C%20decided%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-processed-food-2019-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecut%20down%20on%20UPFs%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20year%20after%20learning%20about%20how%20much%20of%20what%20we%20eat%20is%20considered%20ultra-processed%20and%20the%20potential%20health%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20diet%20high%20in%20UPFs%20has%20been%20linked%20to%20a%20higher%20risk%20of%20developing%20certain%20illnesses%2C%20including%20cardiovascular%20disease%2C%20type%20two%20diabetes%2C%20and%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feating-ultra-processed-foods-ovarian-brain-cancer-risk-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecancers%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20he%20said.%20Studies%20have%20also%20linked%20them%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprocessed-food-makes-us-fat-leads-to-cancer-alternatives-2019-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eovereating%20%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20weight%20gain.%20The%20research%20is%20still%20in%20the%20early%20stages%2C%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20but%20it%20was%20enough%20to%20convince%20him%20to%20make%20a%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20there%20isn't%20a%20set%20definition%20of%20UPFs%2C%20Hobson%20avoids%20foods%20that%20are%20manufactured%20using%20five%20or%20more%20ingredients%2C%20many%20of%20which%20you%20wouldn't%20find%20in%20a%20regular%20kitchen.%20They%20also%20tend%20to%20have%20a%20long%20shelf%20life%2C%20come%20in%20highly%20marketed%20packaging%2C%20and%20are%20made%20to%20be%20ultrapalatable%2C%20Hobson%20said.%20However%2C%20not%20all%20UPFs%20are%20made%20equal%20despite%20being%20painted%20with%20the%20same%20brush.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20plenty%20of%20nutrient-dense%20UPFs%2C%20such%20as%20store-bought%20hummus%2C%20that%20you%20don't%20need%20to%20cut%20out%20simply%20because%20they're%20ultra-processed.%20It's%20about%20limiting%20your%20intake%20where%20you%20can%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHobson%20ate%20healthily%20before%2C%20but%20now%20he%20focuses%20more%20on%20whole%20foods%20and%20cooking%20from%20scratch%20when%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHe%20used%20to%20buy%20bread%20from%20the%20store%2C%20but%20now%20he%20bakes%20his%20own%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20he's%20a%20very%20active%20person%2C%20Hobson%20always%20ensures%20he%20includes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftasty-no-protein-powder-shake-reduce-ultra-processed-foods-diet-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprotein%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20carbohydrates%20on%20his%20breakfast%20plate%2C%20as%20well%20as%20some%20vegetables%20for%20the%20nutrients.%20%26quot%3BI%20pack%20as%20much%20into%20it%20as%20I%20possibly%20can%2C%20so%20every%20mouthful%20of%20food%20is%20as%20nutritious%20as%20it%20possibly%20can%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20what%20he%20eats%20for%20breakfast%20hasn't%20changed%20too%20much%2C%20but%20the%20ingredients%20he%20uses%20to%20make%20it%20have.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20he%20reduced%20his%20UPF%20intake%2C%20he%20typically%20had%20eggs%20on%20toast%20with%20some%20vegetables%2C%20such%20as%20spinach.%20He'd%20use%20store-bought%20sliced%20granary%20bread%2C%20which%20typically%20contains%20additives%20and%20emulsifiers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20he%20makes%20his%20own%20bread%20from%20scratch%20so%20he%20can%20use%20minimally%20processed%20ingredients.%20Sometimes%2C%20he%20makes%20a%20loaf%20of%20bread%20using%20wholemeal%20or%20spelt%20flour%20and%20yeast%20without%20emulsifiers%2C%20which%20he%20slices%20and%20freezes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20if%20he%20has%20less%20time%2C%20he%20might%20make%20a%20flour%20tortilla%20in%20a%20pan%20or%20homemade%20pita%20bread.%20He%20has%20simple%20recipes%20for%20these%20in%20his%20book%20%26quot%3BUnprocess%20Your%20Life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHobson%20makes%20homemade%20granola%20and%20nut%20butter%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20go-to%20for%20Hobson%20was%20yogurt%20with%20a%20fruity%2C%20nutty%20granola%20from%20the%20store%2C%20sliced%20banana%2C%20coconut%20flakes%2C%20dried%20fruit%2C%20and%20nut%20butter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20he%20still%20eats%20this%20regularly%2C%20he%20now%20makes%20both%20the%20granola%20and%20nut%20butter%20himself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20one%20wants%20to%20eat%20plain%20granola%2C%20but%20the%20more%20flavored%20options%20usually%20contain%20other%20ingredients%20such%20as%20sweeteners%20or%20barley%20malt%20extract%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNot%20that%20that's%20necessarily%20bad%2C%20but%20if%20you're%20trying%20to%20reduce%20your%20intake%20of%20ultra-processed%20foods%2C%20then%20trying%20to%20get%20stuff%20as%20natural%20as%20possible%20is%20the%20key%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20He%20makes%20his%20with%20whole%20rolled%20oats%20and%20nuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20it's%20the%20same%20with%20nut%20butter.%20Most%20of%20them%20are%20pretty%20good%2C%20he%20said%2C%20although%20they%20might%20contain%20some%20additives%2C%20but%20he%20prefers%20to%20make%20his%20own.%20%26quot%3BIt%20just%20feels%20like%20it's%20a%20lot%20more%20nutritious%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20makes%20almond%2C%20cashew%2C%20or%20peanut%20butter%20by%20putting%20the%20nuts%20in%20a%20food%20processor%20for%20around%2010%20minutes.%20You%20can%20find%20the%20full%20recipe%20in%20%26quot%3BUnprocess%20Your%20Life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnutritionist-cut-ultra-processed-foods-low-upf-breakfast-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709374322000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e1f291ce7f1785b2e54dc3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnutritionist-cut-ultra-processed-foods-low-upf-breakfast-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Nutritionist%20Rob%20Hobson%20avoids%20ultra-processed%20foods%20after%20learning%20about%20the%20potential%20health%20risks.%20Here's%20what%20he%20eats%20for%20a%20low-UPF%20breakfast.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kschewitz%40businessinsider.com%20(Kim%20Schewitz)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnutritionist-cut-ultra-processed-foods-low-upf-breakfast