20the%20guest%20to%20be%20able%20to%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20available%20showtimes%20to%20work%20within%20their%20schedule%2C%20you%20want%20as%20many%20shows%20as%20possible.%20But%20even%20putting%20it%20on%20two%20screens%20and%20being%20that%20long%2C%20it%20takes%20a%20lot%20longer%20to%20clean%20auditoriums%20between%20shows.%20All%20of%20a%20sudden%2C%20you%20just%20don't%20have%20very%20many%20shows%20available%20to%20your%20guests.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20long%20movies%20aren't%20new.%20In%20the%201950s%2C%20biblical%20tales%20like%20%26quot%3BBen-Hur%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BThe%20Ten%20Commandments%2C%26quot%3B%20both%20of%20which%20stretch%20over%20three%20hours%2C%20were%20the%20blockbusters%20of%20their%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20fast-forward%20to%20modern%20Hollywood%2C%20and%20it%20seems%20like%20every%20IP-fueled%20blockbuster%20is%20trying%20to%20be%20%26quot%3BBen-Hur%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20is%20gunning%20for%20a%20runtime%20to%20match.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ben%20Hur%20MGM%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F56b387a52e526556008b4dce%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22565%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BBen-Hur.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EMGM%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20long%20movie%20that's%20a%20box-office%20smash%20is%20still%20financially%20worth%20it%20for%20a%20movie%20theater%20to%20show.%20But%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fargylle-movie-reviews-critics-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecritical%20and%20commercial%20flop%20like%20%26quot%3BArgylle%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20(two%20hours%20and%2019%20minutes)%2C%20less%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20becomes%20where%20you%20ask%20yourself%2C%20where%20are%20you%20making%20your%20sacrifice%3F%26quot%3B%20Michael%20Barstow%2C%20executive%20vice%20president%20of%20Main%20Street%20Theatres%2C%20which%20operates%20out%20of%20Nebraska%20and%20Iowa%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BIs%20it%20your%207%20p.m.%20set%3F%20Maybe%20you're%20pushing%20your%20start%20to%206%20p.m.%20so%20you%20can%20get%20a%209%20p.m.%20or%209%3A30.%20Or%20you%20focus%20on%20getting%20a%207%20or%207%3A30%20showtime%2C%20but%20then%20you%20get%20a%2010%20p.m.%20late%20show%20and%20tank%20on%20the%209.%20That%20definitely%20is%20a%20thing%20there.%20That%20is%20more%20prevalent%20in%20our%20smaller%20complexes%20of%20three%20or%20four%20screens%2C%20where%20we%20can't%20have%20it%20on%20multiple%20screens.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20executives%20say%20theaters%20lose%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20when%20screen%20times%20are%20taken%20away.%20For%20an%20industry%20that's%20still%20trying%20to%20recover%20from%20the%20pandemic%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F05%2F31%2Fbusiness%2Fmovie-theater-upgrade-pandemic.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20in%202023%20that%20there%20are%20about%205%2C000%20theaters%20running%20in%20the%20US%2C%20compared%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.natoonline.org%2Fdata%2Fus-cinema-sites%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E5%2C869%20in%202019%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20it's%20troubling%20for%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20smaller%20theaters%20are%20thinking%20outside%20the%20box%20to%20make%20a%20buck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJosh%20Frank%2C%20known%20around%20Austin%20for%20his%20Blue%20Starlite%20Drive-In%2C%20recently%20bought%20The%20Eastside%20Cinema%2C%20the%20city's%20last%20single-screen%20movie%20theater.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20he%20programmed%20Hollywood%20titles%2C%20including%20some%20that%20had%20over%20two-and-a-half-hour%20runtimes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNobody%20showed%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20when%20he%20allowed%20community%20organizations%20to%20curate%20his%20offerings%20that%20he%20found%20his%20niche.%20The%20only%20stipulation%20is%20they%20have%20to%20choose%20titles%20that%20are%20under%20two%20hours%20so%20Frank%20can%20have%20two%20showings%20a%20night%20on%20the%20screen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20working%20big%20time%2C%20huge%2C%26quot%3B%20Frank%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20show%20documentaries%2C%20alternative%20films%2C%20it's%20galvanized%20the%20community%20to%20come%20to%20the%20movies%20and%20share%20an%20experience%20with%20their%20friends.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheater%20chains%20can't%20be%20as%20bold.%20They%20can%20only%20wait%20for%20the%20successful%20shorter%20titles%20to%20come%20around%20%E2%80%94%20recent%20hits%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanyone-but-you-studio-rom-com-revival-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAnyone%20but%20You%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BBob%20Marley%3A%20One%20Love%26quot%3B%20were%20under%20two%20hours%20%E2%80%94%20and%20cash%20in%20on%20as%20many%20showtimes%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20an%20art%20to%20making%20movies%20no%20matter%20what%20it%20is%2C%20but%20to%20me%2C%20there's%20an%20even%20more%20interesting%20level%20of%20art%20that%20you%20can%20tell%20a%20story%20and%20do%20it%20successfully%20in%2090%20to%20120%20minutes%2C%26quot%3B%20Vannorsdel%20said.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BIt%20definitely%20would%20benefit%20movie%20theaters.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ELong%20movies%20were%20once%20box-office%20kings.%20Now%20they're%20some%20of%20Hollywood's%20biggest%20busts.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20long%20time%2C%20lengthy%20movies%20were%20tolerated%20because%20they%20were%20successful.%20Though%20the%20industry%20was%20up%20in%20arms%20when%20James%20Cameron%20released%20the%20three-hour%2C%2015-minute-long%20%26quot%3BTitanic%26quot%3B%20in%201997%2C%20it%20went%20on%20to%20become%20the%20highest-grossing%20movie%20of%20all%20time.%20Well%2C%20until%20Cameraon%20came%20out%20with%20%26quot%3BAvatar%26quot%3B%2012%20years%20later%2C%20and%20that%20took%20the%20crown.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20runtime%3F%20Two%20hours%20and%2042%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Titanic%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6080a147354dde0018c0683d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221050%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BTitanic.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3E20th%20Century%20Fox%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20between%20the%20two%20Cameron%20epics%20were%20%26quot%3BLord%20of%20the%20Rings%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BHarry%20Potter%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BPirates%20of%20the%20Caribbean%26quot%3B%20franchises%2C%20all%20of%20which%20clocked%20in%20at%20over%20two%20hours%20and%20were%20hits.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20put%20it%20mildly%3A%20The%20three-hour%2C%2021-minute%20runtime%20for%20%26quot%3BThe%20Lord%20of%20the%20Rings%3A%20The%20Return%20of%20the%20King%26quot%3B%20clearly%20didn't%20hinder%20the%20film's%20success%20%E2%80%94%20it%20brought%20in%20over%20%241.1%20billion%20worldwide%20and%20went%20on%20to%20win%2011%20Oscars%2C%20including%20best%20picture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20recently%2C%20titles%20with%20meaty%20runtimes%20have%20fallen%20flat%20at%20the%20box%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Indiana%20Jones%20and%20the%20Dial%20of%20Destiny%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64a2c4596075be0019c27d5b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BIndiana%20Jones%20and%20the%20Dial%20of%20Destiny.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ELucasfilm%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIndiana%20Jones%20and%20the%20Dial%20of%20Destiny%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20ran%20just%20over%20two%20and%20a%20half%20hours%2C%20underperformed%20to%20the%20point%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Findiana-jones-5-mission-impossible-7-box-office-flops-explained-1235690262%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVariety%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20lost%20Disney%20nearly%20%24100%20million.%20%26quot%3BArgylle%2C%26quot%3B%20with%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdeadline.com%2F2024%2F02%2Fbox-office-argylle-1235812281%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24200%20million%20budget%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20only%20recently%20crossed%20%2475%20million%20worldwide.%20And%20%26quot%3BThe%20Flash%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20movie%20that%20confirmed%20audiences%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-flash-movie-review-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eburned%20out%20on%20superhero%20movies%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20was%20just%20under%20two%20and%20a%20half%20hours%20and%20only%20took%20in%20north%20of%20%24100%20million%20domestically.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20movie%20theater%20experience%20is%20unique%2C%20and%20what%20makes%20it%20great%20is%20you%20are%20a%20captive%20audience%2C%26quot%3B%20Comscore%20senior%20media%20analyst%20Paul%20Dergarabedian%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20if%20you're%20captive%20for%20a%20movie%20that's%20too%20long%20and%20you%20don't%20like%20it%2C%20that's%20not%20any%20fun.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20complaint%20that%20movies%20are%20too%20long%20has%20grown%20louder.%20But%20what%20do%20the%20studios%20have%20to%20say%20about%20it%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20never%20heard%20directly%20from%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Vannorsdel%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFilmmakers%20sign%20a%20contract%20with%20studios%20promising%20to%20make%20movies%20at%20or%20under%20two%20hours%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it's%20never%20enforced%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20was%20able%20to%20have%20a%20frank%20conversation%20on%20the%20topic%20of%20runtimes%20with%20a%20veteran%20studio%20executive%2C%20as%20long%20as%20we%20did%20not%20reveal%20their%20identity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20studio%20exec%20didn't%20hold%20back%2C%20admitting%20that%20%26quot%3Bthere's%20a%20lack%20of%20institutional%20control%26quot%3B%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20studios%20keeping%20running%20times%20in%20check.%20But%20it's%20not%20for%20lack%20of%20trying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20dirty%20secrets%20in%20Hollywood%20is%20that%20every%20studio%20has%20its%20feature%20film%20directors%20sign%20a%20contract%20stating%20they%20will%20deliver%20a%20movie%20with%20a%20runtime%20at%20or%20under%20two%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20those%20contracts%20are%20worth%20as%20much%20as%20the%20paper%20they're%20printed%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20will%20tell%20you%20that%20depending%20on%20the%20director%20and%20depending%20on%20the%20studio%2C%20it's%20probably%20ignored%20more%20than%20it's%20enforced%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20executive%20said%20of%20the%20contract.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20where%20it%20gets%20really%20interesting%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20exec%20added.%20%26quot%3BDo%20the%20people%20who%20write%20the%20checks%20want%20to%20enforce%20it%3F%20And%20that's%20where%20the%20rubber%20meets%20the%20road.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cillian%20Murphy%20as%20J.%20Robert%20Oppenheimer%20in%20%26quot%3BOppenheimer.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b1a3069751e300192a2ed3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22869%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BOppenheimer%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20has%20a%20runtime%20of%20three%20hours.%3Cp%3EUniversal%20Pictures%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20far%20from%20the%20days%20when%20larger-than-life%20studio%20execs%20like%20Jack%20Warner%20and%20David%20O.%20Selznick%20ruled%20Hollywood%20with%20dictator-like%20control.%20Today%2C%20it's%20the%20filmmakers%20who%20have%20the%20leverage%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20if%20they%20have%20a%20money-making%20hit%20under%20their%20belt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20are%20an%20established%20director%2C%20and%20Netflix%20pays%20you%20top%20shelf%20and%20says%2C%20'Go%20forth%2C%20give%20us%20your%20vision%2C'%20They%20love%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20exec%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20what%20complicates%20things.%20A%20director%20comes%20to%20a%20studio%20and%20says%2C%20'Hey%2C%20don't%20fuck%20with%20me%2C%20I'll%20go%20back%20to%20making%20movies%20at%20Netflix.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20streaming%20giant%20has%20been%20able%20to%20seduce%20best%20director%20Oscar%20winners%20like%20Alfonso%20Cuar%C3%B3n%20(2018's%20%26quot%3BRoma%26quot%3B)%2C%20the%20Coen%20brothers%20(2018's%20%26quot%3BThe%20Ballad%20of%20Buster%20Scruggs%26quot%3B)%2C%20and%20Guillermo%20del%20Toro%20(2022's%20%26quot%3BPinocchio%26quot%3B)%2C%20but%20their%20crown%20jewel%20was%20being%20the%20home%20for%20Martin%20Scorsese's%20long-in-development%20gangster%20movie%20%26quot%3BThe%20Irishman%26quot%3B%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20running%20time%3A%20three%20hours%20and%2029%20minutes.%20(Scorsese's%20latest%2C%20%26quot%3BKillers%20of%20the%20Flower%20Moon%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20has%20a%20similar%20runtime%2C%20was%20financed%20by%20Apple%20and%20released%20theatrically%20by%20Paramount).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20exec%20said%20when%20production%20heads%20ask%20what%20runtime%20will%20impact%20the%20number%20of%20showtimes%20per%20day%2C%20his%20answer%20is%20over%20two%20hours%20and%2020%20minutes.%20But%20he%20also%20gives%20a%20piece%20of%20advice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22the%20irishman%20netflix%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5dc9ad14695b587de058d4f5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221622%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Irishman.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ENetflix%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20I%20say%20time%20and%20time%20again%20is%20don't%20worry%20about%20the%20running%20time%20if%20it's%20in%20service%20of%20the%20story%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20exec%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20when%20it's%20not%20in%20service%20of%20the%20story%20%E2%80%94%20then%20you%20need%20to%20worry%20about%20the%20running%20time.%20And%20that's%20not%20an%20unusual%20situation%20to%20be%20in.%20I%20can%20tell%20you%20films%20that%20we've%20released%20in%20the%20last%20year%20and%20yet%20to%20be%20released%20where%20we've%20said%2C%20'We%20have%20to%20find%20eight%20minutes%20to%20take%20out%20of%20this%20movie%20because%20it%20needs%20it.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20difference%20between%20the%20%26quot%3Bwe%20need%20to%20trim%20it%26quot%3B%20note%20in%20today's%20Hollywood%20compared%20to%2015%20years%20ago%20is%20the%20Teflon-like%20swagger%20of%20directors%20today%2C%20the%20exec%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20an%20established%20director%2C%20it's%20a%20tough%20row%20to%20hoe%2C%20but%20guess%20what%3F%20That's%20what%20studio%20heads%20are%20%3Cem%3Esupposed%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20be%20doing%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20exec%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20critical%20part%20of%20their%20job.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20long%20runtimes%20for%20big%20titles%2C%20the%20exec%20doesn't%20see%20change%20coming%20anytime%20soon.%20That%20means%20movie%20theaters%20will%20have%20to%20adapt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20audiences%20have%20generally%20proven%20that%20if%20it's%20the%20right%20case%20or%20the%20right%20filmmaker%2C%20they%20don't%20care%20about%20the%20length%2C%26quot%3B%20Barstow%20from%20Main%20Street%20Theatres%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20always%20come%20at%20it%20as%20we%20are%20going%20to%20bend%20our%20operations%20around%20what%20people%20want%20to%20see.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flong-movies-good-for-streamers-bad-for-movie-theaters-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709374021000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65d52991a610a9069d5ac05d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flong-movies-good-for-streamers-bad-for-movie-theaters-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20a%20streaming%20landscape%20that%20measures%20minutes%20watched%2C%20long%20movies%20and%20TV%20shows%20have%20an%20advantage.%20But%20the%20time%20bloat%20is%20hurting%20movie%20theaters'%20bottom%20lines.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jguerrasio%40insider.com%20(Jason%20Guerrasio)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flong-movies-good-for-streamers-bad-for-movie-theaters-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Meet%20a%20millennial%20DINK%20who%20feels%20like%20an%20outlier%20in%20a%20child-centric%20world%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22millennial%20couple%20on%20the%20beach%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e0d9a6ce7f1785b2e50c9b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMichelle%20(not%20pictured)%20has%20seen%20her%20social%20life%20change%20as%20her%20friends%20have%20kids.%3Cp%3EWestend61%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMichelle%2C%20a%2034-year-old%20DINK%2C%20has%20slowly%20come%20to%20embrace%20a%20childfree%20lifestyle.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDespite%20societal%20pressures%2C%20some%20DINKs%20find%20financial%20stability%20and%20freedom%20in%20their%20decision.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20rise%20in%20DINKs%20may%20continue%20due%20to%20high%20childcare%20costs%20and%20climate%20concerns.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMichelle%20didn't%20always%20know%20she%20wanted%20to%20be%20a%20DINK.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2034-year-old%20said%20it%20wasn't%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebecause%20of%20past%20bad%20experiences%2C%20a%20poor%20relationship%20with%20her%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eparents%2C%20or%20growing%20up%20the%20product%20of%20a%20divorce.%20None%20of%20that%20was%20true%20for%20her%2C%20but%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etoday%20she%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeet-typical-dink-double-income-no-kid-net-worth-retirement-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epart%20of%20a%20double-income%2C%20no-kids%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20or%20DINK%20%E2%80%94%20couple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20North%20Carolina-based%20law%20firm%20partner%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20realization%20kind%20of%20came%20over%20time.%26quot%3B%20She%20had%20always%20been%20under%20the%20assumption%20that%20she%20would%20have%20kids%20because%20%26quot%3Bthat's%20what%20everyone%20did.%26quot%3B%20She%20and%20her%20husband%20had%20some%20conversations%20to%20that%20effect%20when%20they%20were%20younger%20and%20had%20always%20assumed%20they%20might%20have%20kids%20when%20they%20were%20older%2C%20like%20their%20own%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20definitely%20in%20no%20rush%20to%20get%20married%20or%20have%20kids.%20We%20were%20kind%20of%20doing%20our%20own%20thing.%20And%20I%20think%20just%20as%20we%20got%20older%20that%20desire%20just%20never%20really%20hit%20%E2%80%94%20you%20keep%20waiting%20for%20it%20to%20hit%2C%26quot%3B%20Michelle%2C%20whose%20full%20name%20and%20profession%20are%20known%20to%20Business%20Insider%20but%20withheld%20over%20privacy%20concerns%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20she%20told%20her%20husband%20she%20didn't%20know%20if%20she%20was%20ever%20going%20to%20want%20that.%20That%20came%20as%2C%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20she%20saw%20her%20friend%20group%20go%20from%20being%20essentially%20childless%20to%20filled%20with%20parents.%20If%20anything%2C%20that%20solidified%20her%20decision%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20it%20made%20me%20want%20them%20almost%20less%2C%20seeing%20the%20changes%20in%20the%20lifestyles%20that%20my%20friends%20were%20making%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20even%20as%20she%20felt%20the%20social%20media%20and%20societal%20pressure%20to%20follow%20in%20their%20footsteps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20days%2C%20Michelle%20and%20her%20husband%20are%20traveling%2C%20enjoying%20life%2C%20and%20not%20having%20to%20worry%20about%20taking%20care%20of%20anyone%20else.%20They've%20been%20able%20to%20buy%20a%20house%20in%20a%20great%20neighborhood%2C%20install%20a%20pool%2C%20go%20to%20Europe%20and%20on%20safari%2C%20and%20take%20long%20weekend%20trips.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe's%20not%20alone%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdink-couple-retire-early-loves-livestyle-travel-pickleball-freedom-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESeveral%20DINKs%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20ability%20to%20travel%2C%20save%20money%2C%20and%20have%20time%20for%20themselves%20are%20major%20motivators%20for%20staying%20child-free.%20And%2C%20financially%2C%20there%20are%20some%20real%20benefits%20to%20being%20a%20DINK%3A%20Their%20net%20worths%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnet-worth-dink-child-free-couples-win-the-economy-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20outpaced%20that%20of%20other%20family%20structures%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%2C%20for%20some%2C%20being%20a%20DINK%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparents-dinks-winning-childfree-economy-finances-income-vacation-retirement-kids-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20route%20toward%20the%20American%20dream%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20financial%20stability%20and%20putting%20down%20roots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20even%20as%20the%20concept%20of%20being%20a%20DINK%20catches%20on%2C%20it's%20still%20an%20exception%20to%20the%20societal%20rule.%20Studies%20from%20researchers%20Zachary%20P.%20Neal%20and%20Jennifer%20Watling%20Neal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fparents-have-very-warm-feelings-toward-other-parents-heres-why-that-could-be-bad-news-for-the-child-free-190406%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20parents%20favor%20other%20parents%2C%20and%20feel%20more%20warmly%20toward%20them.%20The%20researchers%20found%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20parents%20dislike%20childfree%20people%2C%20but%20it%20does%20mean%20that%20those%20who%20are%20childfree%20might%20end%20up%20feeling%20less%20satisfied%20or%20%26quot%3Bout%20of%20place%26quot%3B%20in%20their%20neighborhoods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFinancially%20we%20can%20put%20that%20money%20toward%20fun%20money%20instead%20of%20childcare%20and%20saving%20for%20college%20and%20all%20those%20types%20of%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20Michelle%20said.%20For%20instance%2C%20they%20were%20able%20to%20take%20a%20spontaneous%20theme%20park%20trip%20recently%20while%20heading%20to%20Orlando%20for%20a%20global%20entry%20interview%20%E2%80%94%20no%20babysitter%20required.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20financials%20are%2C%20it's%20an%20important%20part%20of%20the%20decision%2C%20but%20I%20think%20it's%20not%20the%20only%20part.%20It's%20more%20of%20a%20lifestyle%20trade-off%20than%20a%20financial%20trade-off%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20DINK%20girl%20in%20a%20child-first%20world%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20being%20a%20DINK%20has%20perhaps%20caught%20on%20a%20bit%20more%20in%20the%20US%2C%20it%20still%20feels%20like%20the%20societal%20exception%20to%20the%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Michelle%20and%20her%20spouse's%20parents%20have%20been%20supportive%2C%20the%20couple%20still%20feels%20the%20weight%20of%20a%20culture%20that's%20oriented%20around%20having%20kids.%20When%20she%20moved%20into%20her%20new%20neighborhood%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20a%20neighbor%20came%20over%20and%20asked%20her%20how%20old%20her%20kids%20were%2C%20just%20assuming%20she%20had%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20just%20kind%20of%20this%20expectation%20that%20yeah%2C%20you%20have%20kids%20and%20if%20you%20don't%2C%20there's%20something%20kind%20of%20wrong%20with%20you%2C%20or%20your%20priorities%20are%20misaligned%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20There's%20also%20a%20familiar%20refrain%20%E2%80%94%20one%20that%20many%20DINKs%20come%20up%20against%20%E2%80%94%20that%20it's%20a%20selfish%20decision%20to%20forego%20having%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Michelle%2C%20if%20she%20had%20kids%2C%20she%20said%20she%20might%20be%20resentful%20%E2%80%94%20which%20might%20not%20make%20her%20a%20good%20parent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAren't%20I%20a%20better%20person%20for%20not%20having%20one%20and%20knowing%20my%20boundaries%20than%20maybe%20being%20a%20parent%20that's%20not%20the%20best%20parent%20that%20could%20be%20out%20there%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMichelle%20has%20also%20noticed%20a%20divide%20between%20her%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efriends%20with%20children%20and%20those%20without.%20She%20can't%20make%20spontaneous%20plans%20with%20friends%20who%20are%20parents%2C%20and%20often%20the%20evening%20consists%20of%20hanging%20out%20at%20their%20friends'%20houses%20so%20that%20they%20can%20ensure%20their%20kids%20are%20in%20bed.%20Michelle%20said%20they%20are%20less%20often%20experiencing%20new%20things%20or%20hanging%20out%20in%20large%20groups.%20While%20they%20want%20to%20stay%20close%20to%20their%20friends%20who%20have%20kids%2C%20they%20also%20know%20that%20they%20have%20different%20lifestyles%20and%20priorities%20right%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20a%20couple%20unmarried%20friends%20that%20are%20dating%20here%20that%20I%20think%20we%20weren't%20as%20close%20with%20before%2C%20but%20we%20tend%20to%20spend%20a%20lot%20more%20time%20with%20now%20because%20their%20lifestyles%20line%20up%20and%20their%20availability%20lines%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20a%20DINK%20might%20catch%20on%20even%20more%20soon%20as%20Americans%20contend%20with%20high%20childcare%20costs%20and%20a%20climate%20crisis%20looming.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nerdwallet.com%2Farticle%2Ffinance%2F2024-cost-of-raising-children-report%5C%22%20target