r%20supervisor%20has%20repeatedly%20made%20inappropriate%20advances%2C%20like%20asking%20them%20out%20on%20dates%20and%20sending%20them%20messages%2C%20and%20the%20company%20fails%20to%20address%20the%20situation%2C%20it%20can%20become%20a%20clear-cut%20case%20for%20the%20employee%20to%20take%20legal%20action%20and%20come%20out%20on%20top%2C%20according%20to%20Zambrano.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20is%20easy%2C%20easy%20money%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20employee%2C%20Zambrano%2C%20who%20is%20suing%20the%20musicians%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flizzo-former-dancers-accuse-body-shaming-sexual-harassment-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Lizzo%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-staff-donda-academy-lawsuit-kanye-west-violation-safety-conditions-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Ye%3C%2Fa%3E%20(formerly%20known%20as%20Kanye%20West)%2C%20on%20behalf%20of%20ex-employees%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20an%20under-trained%20human%20resources%20department%20could%20pose%20major%20legal%20troubles%20for%20a%20company%2C%20added%20David%20Gottlieb%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20the%20New%20York%20City-based%20employment%20law%20firm%2C%20Wigdor%20LLP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20working%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhr-leaders-recruiters-hiring-managers-manage-stress-burnout-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHR%20departments%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20companies%20may%20find%20themselves%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Btricky%20position%26quot%3B%20because%20they%20could%20deal%20with%20cases%20that%20involve%20the%20law%2C%20yet%20have%20no%20background%20in%20that%20realm%2C%20Gottlieb%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can%20tell%20by%20the%20way%20things%20transpire%20when%20employees%20call%20%5Bthe%20law%20firm%5D%20with%20complaints%20that%20HR%20is%20not%20well%20trained%20on%20what%20the%20law%20is%2C%20and%20they're%20often%20not%20well%20trained%20on%20what%20the%20company's%20own%20policies%20are%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gottlieb%2C%20who%20is%20one%20of%20the%20lead%20attorneys%20handling%20a%20blockbuster%20class%20action%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrian-flores-racial-discrimination-lawsuit-against-nfl-may-cost-career-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eracial%20discrimination%20lawsuit%20against%20the%20NFL%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20avoid%20legal%20liability%2C%20Gottlieb%20said%20it's%20important%20for%20employers%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20their%20HR%20reps%20undergo%20robust%2C%20yearly%20training%20on%20how%20to%20handle%20complaints%20and%20are%20intimately%20familiar%20with%20the%20company's%20employee%20handbook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGottlieb%20said%20many%20of%20his%20law%20firm's%20cases%20center%20on%20allegations%20of%20retaliation%20as%20opposed%20to%20underlying%20discrimination.%20For%20example%2C%20said%20Gottlieb%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20like%2C%20there's%20some%20issue%2C%20an%20employee%20goes%20to%20HR%20and%20complains%2C%20and%20then%20the%20case%20ends%20up%20being%20about%20what%20happens%20after%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BExposure%20on%20cases%20could%20be%20really%20minimized%20if%20HR%20is%20really%20able%20to%20adequately%20handle%20the%20complaints%2C%26quot%3B%20Gottlieb%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZambrano%20echoed%20those%20remarks%2C%20emphasizing%20the%20importance%20of%20companies%20maintaining%20a%20set%20grievance%20process%20that%20is%20%26quot%3Bobvious%26quot%3B%20to%20employees.%20Employers%20should%20%26quot%3Bact%20quickly%20and%20put%20it%20in%20writing%26quot%3B%20when%20employee%20complaints%20arise%2C%20Zambrano%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20there's%20a%20%26quot%3B50-50%20chance%20of%20liability%26quot%3B%20for%20an%20employer%2C%20the%20company%20%26quot%3Bwill%20absolutely%20throw%20money%26quot%3B%20and%20try%20to%20settle%20the%20case%2C%20said%20Zambrano.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20companies%20want%20to%20settle%2C%26quot%3B%20Zambrano%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20matter%20of%20whether%20the%20employee%20is%20accepting%20the%20money%20as%20quote-unquote%20'enough.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20case%20has%20some%20merit%2C%20employers%20will%20%26quot%3Babsolutely%26quot%3B%20offer%20money%20to%20an%20employee%20pursuing%20legal%20action%2C%20continued%20Zambrano.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20real%20question%20is%20whether%20the%20employee's%20going%20to%20take%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222156%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Money%20with%20a%20gavel%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ddf8226080194819fa6c8b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECompanies%20will%20generally%20look%20to%20settle%20with%20employees%2C%20lawyers%20say.%20%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Being%20a%20jerk%20to%20your%20employees%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20seem%20like%20common%20sense%2C%20but%20treating%20employees%20with%20%26quot%3Bdignity%20and%20respect%26quot%3B%20can%20go%20a%20long%20way%20in%20helping%20to%20keep%20a%20company%20out%20of%20legal%20jeopardy%2C%20according%20to%20Gottlieb.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGottlieb%20said%20his%20law%20firm%20frequently%20gets%20phone%20calls%20from%20employees%20with%20gripes%20that%20their%20performance%20was%20not%20judged%20correctly%20or%20about%20their%20boss%20being%20rude%2C%20demeaning%2C%20or%20even%20condescending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNone%20of%20those%20things%20are%20in%20and%20of%20themselves%20unlawful%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gottlieb.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20he%20said%2C%20those%20calls%20could%20end%20up%20opening%20the%20door%20to%20more%20legally%20inappropriate%20misconduct.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20thing%20that%20I%20find%20over%20and%20over%20and%20over%20again%20is%20people%20call%20a%20lawyer%20when%20they're%20angry%20and%20have%20gripes%20with%20the%20way%20they're%20being%20treated%2C%20and%20then%20during%20the%20course%20of%20a%20conversation%20with%20a%20lawyer%20other%20stuff%20might%20come%20up%20that%20otherwise%20might%20not%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20Gottlieb%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20could%20lead%20to%20what%20a%20potential%20lawsuit%20could%20be%20pinned%20on%2C%20according%20to%20the%20attorney.%20Issues%20employees%20initially%20call%20the%20firm%20with%20may%20be%20totally%20irrelevant%20to%20the%20law%2C%20but%20then%20it%20may%20be%20uncovered%20that%20the%20person%20is%20being%20paid%20unlawfully%2C%20said%20Gottlieb.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20may%20be%20a%20pregnancy%20discrimination%20issue%20that%20the%20person%20wasn't%20even%20thinking%20of%2C%20or%20there%20may%20be%20any%20number%20of%20issues%20that%20they%20weren't%20even%20thinking%20of%2C%26quot%3B%20Gottlieb%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20if%20the%20employer%20just%20treated%20their%20employee%20with%20dignity%20and%20respect%20and%20sensitivity%20such%20that%20they%20didn't%20feel%20the%20need%20to%20call%20a%20lawyer%20in%20the%20first%20place%2C%20that%20would%20be%20a%20way%20to%20avoid%20a%20lot%20of%20issues.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20point%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gottlieb%2C%20%26quot%3Bif%20employers%20treat%20people%20nicely%20with%20dignity%20and%20respect%20and%20compassion%20other%20issues%20that%20lawyers%20might%20be%20able%20to%20identify%20could%20be%20avoided.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Misclassifying%20employees%20as%20exempt%20from%20overtime%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EZambrano%20said%20that%20another%20common%20issue%20he%20encounters%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmisclassifying-gig-workers-independent-contractors-employees-costs-thousands-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemployers%20misclassifying%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20sometimes%20in%20order%20to%20save%20money%20for%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOftentimes%20employees%20will%20be%20misclassified%20as%20salaried%20employees%20exempt%20from%20overtime%20pay%20when%20they%20should%20be%20paid%20an%20hourly%20rate%20with%20overtime%20compensation%2C%20according%20to%20Zambrano.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20another%20mistake%20I%20see%20a%20lot%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Zambrano%2C%20who%20explained%20employers%20regularly%20face%20lawsuits%20for%20overtime%20pay%20violations%20and%20misclassifying%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20personal%20assistants%20will%20go%20through%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20Zambrano%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployees%20will%20routinely%20call%20Zambrano's%20firm%20with%20grievances%20about%20being%20%26quot%3Boverworked%20and%20underpaid%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20what%20I%20am%20learning%20is%20that%20they're%20overworked%20and%20incorrectly%20paid%20%E2%80%94%20they%20should%20be%20paid%20by%20the%20hour%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Zambrano.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20classification%20of%20an%20employee%2C%20it's%20not%20about%20the%20amount%20of%20hours%20an%20employee%20works%2C%20but%20the%20type%20of%20work%20that%20an%20employee%20does%2C%20Zambrano%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20more%20independent%20judgment%20and%20discretion%20you%20have%20in%20the%20execution%20of%20your%20duties%2C%20the%20more%20likely%20you%20are%20correctly%20paid%20on%20a%20salary%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Poor%20handling%20of%20employee%20pregnancy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226092%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cropped%20shot%20of%20a%20woman%20touching%20her%20pregnant%20belly%20while%20sitting%20in%20a%20meeting%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ddfbeece7f1785b2e425d8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223875%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEmployers%20can%20open%20themselves%20up%20to%20legal%20risks%20depending%20on%20how%20they%20handle%20an%20employee's%20pregnancy.%3Cp%3ELaylaBird%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEmployers%20open%20themselves%20up%20to%20legal%20risks%20if%20they%20fail%20to%20properly%20handle%20an%20employee's%20pregnancy%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkers-dont-take-all-parental-leave-because-of-corporate-bias-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eparental%20leave%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20reintegration%20back%20into%20the%20workplace%2C%20according%20to%20Gottlieb.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20an%20employee%20announces%20that%20they're%20pregnant%2C%20that's%20an%20opportunity%20for%20an%20employer%20to%20demonstrate%20their%20commitment%20to%20that%20person%20by%20having%20a%20meaningful%20and%20open%20dialogue%2C%26quot%3B%20Gottlieb%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20Gottlieb%20said%20that%20oftentimes%20he%20finds%20employers%20are%20so%20%26quot%3Bworried%26quot%3B%20about%20talking%20with%20an%20employee%20about%20their%20pregnancy%2C%20fearing%20they%20may%20cause%20offense%2C%20that%20it%20prevents%20employers%20from%20having%20a%20%26quot%3Bmeaningful%26quot%3B%20conversation%20with%20the%20employee%20about%20it%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20harmful%20to%20the%20woman%20to%20not%20be%20able%20to%20make%20an%20informed%20decision%20about%20how%20her%20maternity%20leave%20and%20return%20will%20be%20handled%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawyer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Gottlieb%20said%2C%20there's%20many%20cases%20where%20individuals%20returning%20from%20pregnancy-related%20leave%20find%20themselves%20not%20being%20adequately%20integrated%20back%20into%20the%20workplace%20the%20way%20they%20were%20before%20their%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20someone%20is%20not%20integrated%20back%20into%20the%20workplace%20into%20their%20previous%20role%2C%20that's%20discrimination%20and%20retaliation%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gottlieb.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20employment%20rights%20attorney%2C%20Gottlieb%20said%20that%20pregnancy%20discrimination%20in%20the%20workplace%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20prevalent%20types%20of%20discrimination%20he%20comes%20across.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Reliance%20on%20an%20'automated'%20points-based%20attendance%20tracking%20system%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20June%202020%20report%20by%20the%20worker-advocacy%20group%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abetterbalance.org%2Fmisled-misinformed%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20A%20Better%20Balance%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20an%20estimated%2018%20million%20workers%20across%2066%20US%20employers%2C%20including%20many%20big%20companies%2C%20were%20affected%20by%20points-based%20or%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bno-fault%26quot%3B%20attendance%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMajor%20companies%20such%20as%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fwalmart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Walmart%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Famazon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Amazon%3C%2Fa%3E%20use%20these%20kinds%20of%20controversial%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-workers-reveal-what-its-like-work-largest-retailer-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20points-based%20attendance%20systems%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20track%20worker%20absences%20and%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20fire%20employees%20if%20they%20rack%20up%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20points%20in%20a%20specific%20time%20period%2C%20Zambrano%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-amazon-lawsuits-employee-attendance-tracking-points-system-policy-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20has%20told%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20these%20large%20companies%20are%20just%20really%20stepping%20in%20with%20this%20point%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Zambrano%2C%20explaining%20that%20these%20heavily%20automated%20systems%20%26quot%3Bmake%20a%20lot%20of%20mistakes%26quot%3B%20and%20seemingly%20have%20issues%20filtering%20%26quot%3Ban%20absence%20that%20is%20'unexcused'%20or%20an%20absence%20that%20is%20protected%26quot%3B%20by%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20row%20of%20timecards%20gradually%20turning%20into%20a%20pink%20slip%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cfde60f533b039a884eb57%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPoints-based%20attendance%20policies%20have%20recently%20led%20to%20several%20wrongful%20termination%20lawsuits%20filed%20by%20West%20Coast%20Trial%20Lawyers%20against%20Walmart%20and%20Amazon%3Cp%3ETyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20kinds%20of%20points-based%20attendance%20policies%20have%20recently%20led%20to%20several%20wrongful%20termination%20lawsuits%20filed%20by%20West%20Coast%20Trial%20Lawyers%20against%20both%20Walmart%20and%20Amazon%2C%20according%20to%20Zambrano.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Walmart%20spokesperson%20previously%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20retail%20giant%20will%20continue%20to%20defend%20itself%20against%20the%20litigation.%20An%20Amazon%20spokesperson%20has%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20points%20system%20the%20megacorporation%20uses%20has%20human%20oversight%20and%20that%20the%20company%20works%20with%20its%20employees%20if%20they're%20dealing%20with%20an%20emergency%20or%20any%20unforeseen%20circumstances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZambrano%20said%20his%20firm%20has%20been%20getting%20multiple%20calls%20a%20week%20in%20recent%20months%20from%20people%20reporting%20they%20were%20wrongly%20fired%20from%20their%20jobs%20after%20racking%20up%20too%20many%20points%20for%20absences%2C%20even%20though%20their%20leave%20should%20have%20been%20protected%20or%20was%20already%20cleared%20with%20managers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20stuff%20is%20happening%20very%20routinely%2C%20and%20people%20are%20just%20being%20laid%20off%20just%20because%20they%20hit%20these%20points%2C%20and%20there's%20no%20one%20fixing%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Zambrano%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20absolutely%20crazy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcommon-mistakes-employers-companies-result-settlements-workers-lawsuits-attorneys-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709373601000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65de263490413ab8e1d72c15%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcommon-mistakes-employers-companies-result-settlements-workers-lawsuits-attorneys-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Business%20Insider%20spoke%20with%20high-profile%20employment%20rights%20lawyers%20about%20mistakes%20companies%20repeatedly%20make%20that%20lead%20to%20big%20payouts%20to%20their%20workers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nmusumeci%40businessinsider.com%20(Natalie%20Musumeci)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcommon-mistakes-employers-companies-result-settlements-workers-lawsuits-attorneys-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22No%20Government%20Medical%20College%20Set%20Up%20in%20Gujarat%20After%201995%3A%20BJP%20State%20Govt%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02151450%2FUntitled-design-23-1.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20There%20has%20not%20been%20a%20single%20government%20medical%20college%20set%20up%20in%20Gujarat%20since%201995%2C%20as%20per%20the%20Gujarat%20government%E2%80%99s%20own%20information%20in%20the%20State%20assembly.%20But%20four%20private%20medical%20colleges%20have%20been%20granted%20permissions%20last%20year%2C%20in%202023.%20Of%20the%20508%20new%20nursing%20schools%20and%20colleges%20set%20up%20over%20two%20years%2C%20only%20one%20was%20on%20the%20state%20government%E2%80%99s%20initiative%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fnation%2F2024%2FMar%2F02%2Fno-new-govt-med-colleges-built-in-gujarat-since-95-but-nod-to-4-in-23%23%3A~%3Atext%3DBhavnagar%2520in%25201995.-%2CThus%252C%2520the%2520Gujarat%2520government%2520has%2520not%2520had%2520a%2520single%2520government%2Ca%2520go%252Dahead%2520in%25202023.%5C%22%3Ereports%20%3Cem%3EThe%20New%20Indian%20Express.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20BJP%20state%20government%2C%20in%20power%20almost%20continuously%20since%201995%2C%20but%20for%20a%20brief%20interlude%2C%20said%20in%20a%20written%20reply%20that%20six%20government%20medical%20colleges%20are%20operating%20in%20the%20state.%20The%20first%20was%20established%20in%20Ahmedabad%20in%201871%20and%20the%20last%20in%20Bhavnagar%20in%201995.%20This%20was%20in%20response%20to%20Congress%20MLA%20Amit%20Chavda%E2%80%99s%20question%20in%20the%20Assembly%20on%20Thursday%2C%20February%2029.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reply%20also%20says%20no%20government%20medical%20colleges%20were%20approved%20in%202022%20or%202023%2C%20but%20four%20private%20medical%20colleges%20were%20given%20the%20green%20signal%20last%20year.%20%C2%A0The%20newspaper%20reports%20that%20in%202022%2C%20%E2%80%9Cfive%20medical%20colleges%20run%20by%20the%20Gujarat%20Medical%20Education%20%26amp%3B%20Research%20Society%20(a%20registered%20trust%20of%20the%20Gujarat%20government)%20got%20government%20approval.%E2%80%9D%20Also%2C%20%E2%80%9Cin%20the%20past%20two%20years%2C%20no%20new%20government%20or%20grant-aided%20college%20for%20Ayurveda%20and%20Homeopathy%20degrees%20has%20been%20sanctioned%20in%20the%20state.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJust%20one%20public%20nursing%20school%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20another%20question%20raised%20by%20Congress%20MLA%20Ganiben%20Thakor%2C%20the%20BJP%20government%20stated%20that%20508%20new%20nursing%20schools%20and%20colleges%20have%20opened%20in%20the%20state%20in%20the%20last%20two%20years%2C%20but%20of%20the%20508%2C%20only%20one%20is%20a%20public%20nursing%20institution.%20The%20remaining%20507%20were%20all%20private%20colleges.%20In%202023-24%2C%20of%20a%20total%20of%20315%20institutes%20established%2C%20only%20one%2C%20MSC%20Nursing%20Government%20College%2C%20was%20government-run.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHealth%20Minister%20Rushikesh%20Patel%20claimed%20that%20the%20government%20intends%20to%20establish%20a%20medical%20college%20in%20each%20district.%20%E2%80%9CBy%202027%2C%20the%20government%20aims%20to%20increase%20the%20number%20of%20medical%20seats%20at%20undergraduate%20and%20postgraduate%20levels%20to%2012%2C200%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20health%20minister%20is%20quoted%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20fees%20of%20government%20colleges%20must%20be%20low%20compared%20to%20private%20colleges%20to%20enable%20the%20poor%20and%20middle-class%20students%20to%20become%20doctors%2C%20but%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20has%20not%20established%20any%20new%20government%20medical%20college%20in%20the%20last%2029%20years%20because%20this%20government%20cares%20only%20for%20rich%20and%20industrialists%2C%E2%80%9D%20Amit%20Chavda%2C%20Leader%20of%20Opposition%20in%20the%20Gujarat%20Assembly%20is%20quoted%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPublic%20medical%20institutions%20outside%20Gujarat%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAcross%20the%20country%2C%20as%20the%20country%20gears%20up%20for%20the%20general%20elections%20due%20in%20a%20few%20weeks%2C%20the%20BJP%20government%20has%20amped%20up%20its%20publicity%20but%20there%20has%20been%20a%20sharp%20debate%20on%20exactly%20how%20many%20public%20medical%20institutions%2C%20especially%20AIIMS%2C%20the%20BJP%20government%20has%20been%20claiming%20it%20has%20set%20up.%20Five%20were%20inaugurated%20by%20PM%20Modi%20across%20India%2C%20but%20there%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpm-modi-to-inaugurate-5-aiims-next-week-but-are-they-new%5C%22%3Equestions%20about%20how%20%E2%80%98new%E2%80%99%20they%20are%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20of%20multiple%20inaugurations%20they%20have%20seen.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fpm-modi-aiims-functioning%5C%22%3Ereported%20last%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20partially%20constructed%20AIIMS%20being%20declared%20as%20complete%20institutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709373542000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02151450%2FUntitled-design-23-1.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fno-government-medical-college-set-up-in-gujarat-after-1995-bjp-state-govt%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20BJP%20government%2C%20in%20power%20since%201995%2C%20has%20said%20in%20the%20Assembly%20that%20the%20last%20public%20medical%20college%20in%20the%20state%20was%20in%20Bhavnagar%20in%201995.%20Of%20508%20nursing%20institutions%20in%20the%20state%20in%20the%20last%20two%20years%2C%20only%20one%20is%20a%20public%20institution.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fno-government-medical-college-set-up-in-gujarat-after-1995-bjp-state-govt%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Peace%2C%20music%2C%20and%20memories%3A%20As%20the%201960s%20fade%2C%20historians%20scramble%20to%20capture%20Woodstock's%20voices%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709373182000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108162013%2Cimgsize-1709440.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fpeace-music-and-memories-as-the-1960s-fade-historians-scramble-to-capture-woodstocks-voices%2Farticleshow%2F108161066.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cim