ment%20(CSE)%20%E2%80%93%20the%20data%20for%20which%20is%20drawn%20from%20the%20UN-backed%20Sustainable%20Development%20Report%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20India%20has%20improved%20its%20ranking%20from%20the%20previous%20year%20%E2%80%93%20it%20was%20121st%20in%202022%20%E2%80%93%20it%20still%20trails%20countries%20like%20Bhutan%20(61st%2C%20the%20best%20in%20South%20Asia)%2C%20the%20Maldives%20(68th)%2C%20Sri%20Lanka%20(83rd)%2C%20Nepal%20(99th)%20and%20Bangladesh%20(101st).%20Pakistan%20is%20at%20128th%20while%20Afghanistan%20is%20158th.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%20is%20behind%20many%20South%20Asian%20countries%20in%20(its%20performance%20towards)%20achieving%20its%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goals%2C%20and%20it%20seems%20that%20its%20economic%20process%20has%20not%20adequately%20rubbed%20off%20on%20the%20parameters%20linked%20to%20broad%20societal%20quality%20of%20life%20agendas%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20former%20UN%20undersecretary-general%20for%20economic%20and%20social%20affairs%2C%20Nitin%20Desai%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Findia-ranks-112th-on-progress-towards-un-mandated-sustainable-development-goals-in-2023%2Fcid%2F2004138%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Telegraph%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20score%20of%2063.45%25%20in%202023%2C%20India%20marked%20a%20small%20improvement%20over%20the%20previous%20year%E2%80%99s%2060.3%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20specific%20parameters%20of%20%E2%80%9Creducing%20inequalities%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Clife%20on%20land%E2%80%9D%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20performance%20has%20deteriorated.%20Life%20on%20land%20relates%20to%20conserving%20biodiversity%2C%20where%20India%20is%20close%20to%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20table.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20country%20has%20also%20fared%20poorly%20on%20parameters%20such%20as%20%E2%80%9Csustainable%20cities%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cequality%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cclean%20water%20and%20sanitation%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E