show%2F108151489.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Finjured-survivors-of-gaza-aid-chaos-say-israeli-forces-shot-at-them%2Famp_articleshow%2F108151489.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Finjured-survivors-of-gaza-aid-chaos-say-israeli-forces-shot-at-them%2Famp_articleshow%2F108151489.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Many%20Iranians%20boycott%20vote%2C%20despite%20officials'%20pleas%20and%20roses%20at%20polls%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709347410000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108151939%2Cimgsize-1392927.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fmany-iranians-boycott-vote-despite-officials-pleas-and-roses-at-polls%2Farticleshow%2F108151572.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F108151572.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EIran's%20parliamentary%20elections%20saw%20low%20turnout%20as%20many%20people%20protested%20against%20the%20government.%20Social%20media%20pleas%20and%20rose%20distribution%20failed%20to%20increase%20voter%20participation.%20Reformist%20and%20conservative%20factions%20faced%20a%20boycott.%20Iranians%20demanded%20change%20beyond%20existing%20political%20parties.%20State%20television%20presented%20a%20different%20narrative.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fmany-iranians-boycott-vote-despite-officials-pleas-and-roses-at-polls%2Farticleshow%2F108151572.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20Contemporary%20Hindi%20Literature%20Tells%20Us%20About%20the%20Politics%20of%20Hate%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26130445%2FIMG_2925-3.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBen%20Okri%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CStorytellers%20are%20the%20singing%20conscience%20of%20a%20land%2C%20the%20unacknowledged%20guides.%E2%80%9D%20For%20him%2C%20the%20life%20of%20a%20nation%20%E2%80%93%20its%20health%2C%20its%20spiritual%20strength%20%E2%80%93%20can%20be%20deduced%20from%20the%20stories%20the%20nation%20tells%2C%20the%20stories%20it%20suppresses%2C%20the%20stories%20it%20sanctions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnlike%20historians%20who%20work%20with%20the%20past%3B%20the%20storyteller%E2%80%99s%20job%20is%20to%20weave%20individual%20sufferings%20into%20the%20fabric%20of%20time%2C%20connecting%20the%20past%2C%20the%20present%20and%20the%20future.%20History%20mostly%20revolves%20around%20leaders%2C%20winners%2C%20kings.%20It%20condenses%20individual%20grief%20and%20trauma%20in%20objective%20reports%20and%20cold%20statistics.%20But%20for%20the%20storyteller%2C%20ordinary%20suffering%20is%20supreme.%20In%20violent%20times%20like%20the%20Partition%2C%20war%2C%20communal%20riots%2C%20the%20voices%20that%20get%20erased%20due%20to%20fear%20and%20circumstance%2C%20and%20the%20experiences%20that%20are%20reduced%20to%20footnotes%20form%20the%20writers%E2%80%99%20material.%20Their%20task%20is%20to%20observe%2C%20listen%20and%20put%20the%20unspeakable%20down.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENo%20wonder%2C%20literature%20remains%20the%20place%20where%20ordinary%20grief%2C%20disenchantment%2C%20and%20suffering%20get%20the%20fundamental%20dignity%20of%20being%20recorded%20and%20memorialised.%20That%20literature%20became%20an%20important%20way%20to%20memorialise%20the%20bewildering%20rupture%20of%20Partition%20is%20significant.%20It%20is%20also%20significant%20that%20more%20than%20English%2C%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ebhashas%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3EHindi%2C%20Urdu%2C%20Bangla%20%E2%80%93%20spoke%20most%20eloquently%20about%20Partition%20horrors.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMother%20tongues%20are%20the%20languages%20of%20our%20dreams%20and%20our%20mourning.%20Noted%20historian%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F25817920%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3EMushirul%20Hasan%20says%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Partition%20literatures%20constitute%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6a%20cultural%20archive%20of%20first-hand%20information%2C%20experiences%20and%20vivid%20impressions..%E2%80%9D%20without%20which%2C%20the%20anguish%2C%20uncertainty%2C%20loss%2C%20confusion%20faced%20by%20those%20afflicted%2C%20can%20never%20be%20understood.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hansrajcollege.ac.in%2FhCPanel%2Fuploads%2Felearning%2Felearning_document%2F(Contemporary_South_Asia)_Gyanendra_Pandey_-_Remembering_Partition__Violence%2C_Nationalism_and_History_in_India-Cambridge_University_Press_(2002).pdf%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3EGyanendra%20Pandey%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESubaltern%20School%20of%20Humanities%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20calls%20the%20inability%20of%20History%20to%20record%20ordinary%20suffering%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20chasm%20between%20history%20and%20memory.%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESubaltern%20School%20of%20Humanities%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20founded%20by%20Ranajit%20Guha%2C%20Shahid%20Amin%2C%20Gyanendra%20Pandey%20and%20others%2C%20asserts%20that%20this%20chasm%20can%20be%20bridged%20only%20by%20dipping%20into%20oral%20histories%2C%20written%20first%20person%20accounts%2C%20songs%2C%20folklore%20and%20literature%20%E2%80%93%20where%20the%20emotional%20and%20psychological%20echoes%20of%20collective%20violence%20continue%20to%20reverberate.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20his%20preface%20to%20the%20four%20volume%20anthology%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EStories%20about%20the%20Partition%20of%20India%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F4408572%3FsearchText%3Dalok%2520Bhalla%2520partition%26searchUri%3D%252Faction%252FdoBasicSearch%253FQuery%253Dalok%252BBhalla%252Bpartition%26ab_segments%3D0%252Fbasic_search_gsv2%252Fcontrol%26refreqid%3Dfastly-default%253Abd3897e034b4ee99558462b86c5b08b3%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3EAlok%20Bhalla%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CPartition%20fictions%20bears%20witness%20to%20the%20sorrows%20of%20the%20exiled%E2%80%A6but%20refuse%20to%20surrender%20to%20any%20bullying%20ideology%E2%80%A6.there%20are%20hardly%20any%20communally%20charged%20stories%20preaching%20hate%20and%20calling%20for%20annihilation%20of%20other%20religious%20groups%20written%20in%20any%20of%20the%20languages%20of%20the%20subcontinent.%E2%80%9D%20Hindi-Urdu%20novelists%20of%20post%20partition%20era%20%E2%80%93%20Bhishm%20Sahani%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETamas%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E)%2C%20Rahi%20Masoom%20Raza%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAdha%20Gaon%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E)%2C%20Yashpal%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EJhootha%20Sach%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E)%2C%20Krishna%20Sobti%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EZindaginama%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Gujarat%20Pakistan%20se%20Gujarat%20Hindustan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E)%2C%20Amrita%20Pritam%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPinjar%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E)%2C%20Rajinder%20Bedi%2C%20Kartar%20Singh%20Duggal%2C%20Joginder%20Paul%2C%20Rajee%20Seth%2C%20Intizar%20Hussain%2C%20and%20Qurratulain%20Hyder%20%E2%80%93%20likewise%20chronicle%20the%20violence%2C%20the%20silence%2C%20and%20the%20trauma%2C%20along%20with%20the%20loss%2C%20the%20bewilderment.%20This%20literary%20feast%20is%20not%20surprising%2C%20given%20that%20modernist%20Hindi-Urdu%20literature%20came%20of%20age%20in%20the%20early%20decades%20of%20the%2020th%20century%2C%20and%20determined%20its%20role%20through%20the%20founding%20of%20the%20Progressive%20Writer%E2%80%99s%20Group%20or%20PWG%2C%20in%201935%2C%20by%20Premchand%2C%20Nirala%2C%20Manto%2C%20Chugtai%20and%20several%20others.%20This%20ethos%20of%20%E2%80%9Ca%20critical%20engagement%20with%20the%20political-social%20upheavals%20of%20the%20time%E2%80%9D%20has%20influenced%20subsequent%20generations%20of%20writers%20as%20well.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EContemporary%20Hindi%20literature%20constitutes%20an%20archive%20of%20experiences%20of%20contemporary%20religion%2C%20caste%2C%20gender%20and%20ecological%20violences.%20It%20catalogues%20the%20effect%20of%20violent%20public%20discourse%20on%20private%20spaces%20and%20on%20individual%20psyches.%20They%20talk%20of%20channels%20of%20greed%20irrigated%20by%20violent%20discourse.%20Between%20their%20pages%2C%20individual%20anxiety%2C%20grief%2C%20social%20uncertainty%20and%20absurdity%20get%20a%20place%20to%20be.%20They%20link%20economic%20liberalisation%20with%20the%20politics%20incubated%20by%20it.%20They%20show%20how%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20bogey%20enemy%20is%20essential%20to%20corral%20and%20fence%20off%20of%20the%20financial%20gains%20and%20to%20ensure%20that%20patriarchy%20and%20caste%20hegemonies%20stay%20intact.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EInvasion%20of%20politics%20in%20intimate%20spaces%20in%20Geetanjali%20Shree%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cb%3E%3Ci%3EHamara%20Shahar%20Us%20Baras%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20had%20started%20talking%20as%20if%20there%20really%20were%20only%20two%20identities%20and%20everything%20was%20either%20Hindu%20or%20Muslim.%E2%80%9D%20(translation%20mine.)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGeetanjali%20Shree%E2%80%99s%20narrator%20in%20this%20novel%2C%20tells%20the%20story%20of%20%E2%80%98that%20year%E2%80%99%20when%20her%20city%20starts%20witnessing%20frequent%20communal%20disturbances.%20A%20time%20of%20uncertainty%20and%20dread%20when%20the%20old%20and%20tried%20and%20tested%20ways%20of%20living%20got%20kicked%20aside.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENarrated%20in%20a%20breathless%2C%20fragmented%20voice%20by%20a%20narrator%20who%20says%20she%E2%80%99s%20not%20a%20writer%20but%20someone%20who%20is%20simply%20taking%20down%20whatever%20people%20say%2C%20the%20novel%E2%80%99s%20narrative%20style%20mimics%20the%20external%20situation%20of%20the%20fragmentation%20in%20the%20city.%20The%20focus%20is%20not%20on%20incidents%2C%20but%20on%20fleshing%20out%20the%20shocked%20silence%2C%20the%20paralytic%20huddle%20of%20intellectuals%2C%20and%20the%20tongue-tied%20incomprehension%20of%20professional%20writers%20who%20do%20not%20know%20how%20to%20respond.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20year%20she%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Hindus%20left%20amicability.%E2%80%9D%20The%20Jagdambe%20Math%20that%20lay%20hidden%20in%20a%20shrubbery%20on%20one%20side%20of%20a%20playground%20across%20from%20their%20balcony%2C%20emerged%20from%20the%20shrubbery%20%E2%80%93%20first%20with%20a%20saffron%20flag%20on%20top%2C%20then%20with%20a%20mela%2C%20then%20a%20loudspeaker%2C%20that%20got%20louder%20and%20louder%20in%20its%20chants%20and%20slogans%20%E2%80%93%20and%20started%20marching%20over%20the%20playground.%20The%20narrator%20who%20is%20neither%20a%20professor%20nor%20an%20intellectual%20like%20her%20friends%2C%20goes%20on%20trying%20to%20write%20how%20the%20events%20outside%20are%20wrecking%20the%20most%20intimate%20and%20sacred%20parts%20of%20them.%20Whether%20they%20talk%20or%20studiously%20avoid%20talking%20of%20events%2C%20Shruti%20and%20Hanif%2C%20the%20interfaith%20couple%2C%20and%20Sharad%20and%20Hanif%20colleagues%20and%20friends%2C%20find%20the%20air%20between%20them%20vitiated.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20derailment%20of%20ordinary%20lives%20in%20Rakesh%20Kayasth%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cb%3E%3Ci%3ERambhakt%20Rangbaz%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESet%20in%20the%20backdrop%20of%20imminent%20rath%20yatra%20in%20a%20small%20town%20mohalla%20Aramganj%2C%20the%20novel%20deconstructs%20Mandal-Kamandal%20politics%20of%20the%20heartland%20through%20the%20story%20of%20a%20popular%20Ram%20worshipping%20Muslim%20tailor%2C%20Ashiq%20Rangbaz%2C%20whose%20life%20is%20thrown%20into%20chaos%20as%20an%20altered%20discourse%20takes%20over%20the%20mohalla.%20People%20he%20has%20been%20with%20all%20his%20life%2C%20suddenly%20start%20asking%20new%20questions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAkhilesh%20had%20asked%20on%20his%20face%2C%20%E2%80%98We%20all%20think%20of%20you%20as%20a%20Hindu.%20Who%20do%20you%20think%20you%20are%2C%20bey%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20answer%20came%2C%20%E2%80%98Whatever%20my%20Ram%20ji%20has%20made%20me%2C%20I%20am%20that%20only.%20Why%20do%20you%20take%20tension%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98Meaning%2C%20Ram%20ji%20made%20you%20a%20mulla%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98Yes%2C%20think%20that%20only.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIncredible%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20things%20you%20say.%20Is%20that%20even%20possible%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98When%20a%20chutiya%20like%20you%20can%20be%20made%20by%20Ram%20ji%2C%20then%20why%20not%20me%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20not%20easy%20to%20trap%20Rangbaz%20with%20mere%20questions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20so%2C%20why%20at%20all%20are%20these%20questions%20being%20asked%3F%20Why%20has%20their%20frequency%20gone%20up%20all%20of%20a%20sudden%3F%20Aramganj%20walas%20do%20not%20know%20why%2C%20but%20they%20suddenly%20have%20too%20many%20questions%20about%20Muslims%20in%20their%20hearts.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E(translation%20mine)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20Greek%20chorus%20of%20small%20town%20characters%20and%20their%20antics%20reveal%20diverse%20views%20on%20the%20emerging%20politics.%20It%20is%20not%20as%20though%20communal%20mindsets%20did%20not%20exist%20earlier%20in%20this%20mohalla%20beset%20with%20feudal%2C%20patriarchal%20and%20casteist%20characters%3B%20but%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Esuddenly%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20they%20acquire%20a%20rallying%20point%20and%20a%20face.%20The%20real%20question%20is%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20whether%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethis%20newfound%20Hindu%20unity%20imply%20an%20end%20of%20caste-divisions%20or%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Esimply%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20a%20scuttling%20of%20caste%20politics%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EUday%20Prakash%3A%20The%20absurd%20face%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20growth%20story%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENo%20contemporary%20Hindi%20writer%20better%20captures%20the%20cauldron%20of%20desperate%20inequity%20that%20the%20fastest%20growing%20economy%20and%20world%E2%80%99s%20fourth%20largest%20consumer%20market%20is%2C%20than%20Uday%20Prakash.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHis%20translator%20Jason%20Grunebaum%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CTo%20read%20Uday%20Prakash%20is%20to%20witness%20profound%20displacement.%20It%20is%20a%20displacement%20unleashed%20by%20forces%20both%20imported%20and%20indigenous%2C%20in%20the%20India%20of%20today%20%E2%80%93%20global%2C%20hungry%2C%20late-stage%20capitalism%20steeped%20in%20centuries-old%20caste%20oppression%20%E2%80%93%20inscribed%20on%20the%20likes%20of%20sweepers%2C%20weavers%2C%20semi-retired%20judges%2C%20typesetters%2C%20servants%20returned%20from%20the%20dead%2C%20sick%20slum%20kids%2C%20and%20others%20unable%2C%20or%20unwilling%2C%20to%20fall%20in%20line.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPrakash%E2%80%99s%20surreal%20dystopias%20string%20together%20news%20headlines%2C%20history%20and%20poetry.%20There%20is%20no%20justice%2C%20poetic%20or%20otherwise%20in%20the%20economic%20dystopias%20of%20those%20living%20in%20slums%20and%20footpaths%20of%20society.%20Life%20is%20cheap%2C%20people%20are%20always%20dying.%20They%20drink%20discarded%20poison%20syrups%20and%20die%2C%20get%20killed%20in%20encounter%20killings%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETepchu%2C%20Dilli%20ki%20Diwar%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E)%2C%20commit%20suicide%20due%20to%20caste%20oppression%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMohandas%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E)%2C%20die%20screaming%20when%20forced%20to%20doctor%20post-mortem%20reports%2C%20or%20simply%20vanish.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20spiffy%2C%20beautified%2C%20segregated%20city%2C%20in%20Geetanjali%20Shree%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cb%3E%3Ci%3EYahan%20Haathi%20Rahte%20The%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20young%20employee%20in%20a%20multinational%20is%20intrigued%20by%20the%20figure%20of%20an%20old%20lady%20who%20he%20often%20comes%20across%20on%20the%20beautified%20promenade.%20Once%20elephants%20bathed%20on%20ghats%20where%20this%20promenade%20now%20exists.%20Who%20is%20she%3F%20From%20which%20part%20of%20the%20city%3F%20This%20side%20or%20that%20side%3F%20After%20the%20riots%2C%20the%20spiffy%20city%20has%20been%20split%20in%20two.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20riots%20made%20this%20city%20famous.%20Well%2C%20not%20the%20riots%20themselves%2C%20but%20the%20glitter%20and%20glamor%20that%20most%20definitely%20resulted%20from%20the%20riots.%20Had%20the%20city%20not%20been%20so%20jammed%20and%20jumbled%2C%20chaos%20would%20not%20have%20broken%20out.%20And%20if%20chaos%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20broken%20out%2C%20there%20would%20never%20have%20been%20such%20a%20cleanup.%20The%20factions%20were%20divided%20so%20neatly%20the%20city%20shone.%20One%20faction%20this%20side%20of%20the%20river%2C%20one%20that%20side%2C%20and%20each%20clearly%20recognizable%20in%20its%20place.%20As%20though%20factories%20had%20been%20built%20on%20either%20side%20to%20manufacture%20each%20faction%E2%80%99s%20particular%20costumes%20and%20masks%2C%20and%20absolutely%20everyone%20appeared%20only%20in%20their%20respective%20attire.%20Everyone%20wore%20their%20assigned%20uniform%2C%20and%20everyone%20wore%20the%20same%20mask.%20This%20side%20wore%20theirs%2C%20that%20side%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ew%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eore%20theirs.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwordswithoutborders.org%2Fread%2Farticle%2F2023-01%2Fonce-elephants-lived-here-part-one-geetanjali-shree-daisy-rockwell%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETranslation%20by%20Daisy%20Rockwell.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20new%20found%20glamour%20of%20malls%2C%20high-rises%20and%20multiplexes%20sits%20on%20the%20ruins%20of%20the%20chaotic%2C%20composite%2C%20open-armed%20city%20that%20was.%20Even%20the%20plate-glassed%20office%20where%20the%20protagonist%20works%2C%20was%20once%20a%20haveli%20belonging%20to%20the%20same%20old%20woman%20whose%20bold%20craziness%20makes%20the%20homogenized%20new%20world%20uneasy.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETerrorizing%20any%20designated%20%E2%80%98other%E2%80%99%20to%20appropriate%20their%20land%20and%20Capital%20for%20%E2%80%98development%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98beautification%E2%80%99%20is%20a%20prerequisite%20for%20such%20selective%2C%20sterile%20growth.%20The%20true%20face%20of%20neoliberal%20capitalistic%20%E2%80%98development%E2%80%99%C2%A0%20is%20made%20visible%20in%20this%20story%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp